12 auribus· · · adcommodata: Virtually the same phrase is ap- plied to Seneca by Tac. Ann. XIII 3 oratio a Seneca composita multum cultus (sc. praetulit) ut fuit illi viro ingenium amoenum ot temporis eius auribus adcommodatum. Cf. also Cic. de orat. II 38, 159 oratio multitudinis auribus est adcommodanda—ipeum quoque: i. e. one would not be led to expect this knowledge in one whose speeches so rarely furnished any evidence of its existence.
